  "prompt": "What are the best available social media analytics tool?",
  "response": "There are numerous social media analytics tools available in the market, each offering unique features and capabilities. Some of the best tools include:\n\n1. **Hootsuite Analytics**: Hootsuite is a comprehensive social media management platform that includes robust analytics features. It allows you to monitor and analyze the performance of your social media campaigns across multiple platforms.\n\n2. **Sprout Social**: Sprout Social offers detailed analytics and reporting features, allowing you to track engagement, audience growth, and the overall performance of your social media efforts.\n\n3. **Google Analytics**: While not exclusively a social media analytics tool, Google Analytics can be used to track the impact of social media on your website traffic and conversions.\n\n4. **Buffer Analyze**: Buffer Analyze provides in-depth insights into your social media performance, including engagement rates, follower growth, and the best times to post.\n\n5. **Talkwalker**: Talkwalker is a powerful social media analytics and monitoring tool that offers real-time data and insights across multiple platforms. It\u2019s particularly useful for tracking brand mentions and sentiment analysis.\n\n6. **Brandwatch**: Brandwatch provides advanced analytics and consumer insights, helping you understand your audience and the impact of your social media activities.\n\n7. **Socialbakers**: Socialbakers offers a suite of analytics tools that help you measure the performance of your social media campaigns and optimize your strategy.\n\n8. **HubSpot Social Media Analytics**: HubSpot\u2019s social media analytics tool integrates with its broader marketing platform, allowing you to track the effectiveness of your social media efforts in the context of your overall marketing strategy.\n\nWhen choosing a social media analytics tool, consider your specific needs, the platforms you use, and your budget. Many of these tools offer free trials or demo versions, so you can test them out before committing.",
